column5:
I attempted to install the prop nut anode but found the standard bolt included with the anode is too short. It's possible I didn't have the right size anode as well, either way that's on me. I'll acquire some more options and try again this week.

I was able to mostly get around the trim tab using a small bottle brush.
Attempted install of slim shaft collar, not enough clearance.
Barnacles widespread. Paint has failed, missing.
Did not have the correct anode in stock. Ordering today, will try again.
Using a much coarser brush to get the deep algae out of the paint,  it’s a process over multiple services.
